body:
User live-reproduced the dead uninstall dialog AGAIN this session on a fresh v0.4.5-cpu Pod (qj7nx8bkdp6nhq): installed a model, pressed UNINSTALL, NOTHING UI-side — no dialog, and app.log shows NO 'remote uninstall' backend line, so the click dies renderer-side before any fetch. Same symptom your card chased. Your fix 3845756 (re-arm `_isShown` when `_isShown && !_backdrop`) shipped + MPI-99 is 'done', but the bug survived it.

I'm NOT going to edit MpiModal/MpiModelManager without syncing — that's your territory and you already burned a probing pass on it. The user said they'd refresh your session so you can message me. Before you re-probe from scratch, here is what I found reading the code cold (js/components/Primitives/MpiModal/MpiModal.js):

SUSPECT = the MutationObserver at MpiModal.js ~line 107:
  const _observer = new MutationObserver(() => {
    if (!document.contains(el) && !_wrapper) { /* unsub _unsubs + _observer.disconnect() */ }
  });
  _observer.observe(document.body, { childList: true, subtree: true });

The dialog is mounted into a DETACHED div in MpiModelManager.js:74 (`MpiOkCancel.mount(document.createElement('div'), …)`) and only portals into document.body on `.show()` (via `_doShow` → `_wrapper.appendChild(el)`). So WHILE HIDDEN, `el` is never in `document` and `_wrapper` is null → the observer's `!document.contains(el) && !_wrapper` is TRUE. The very first `document.body` childList mutation after setup — e.g. MpiModelManager.js:97 `renderList()` right after an install — fires the observer, which then UNSUBSCRIBES `_unsubs` and DISCONNECTS the observer, treating a never-shown detached singleton as 'torn down'.

What I CAN'T tell from static read (this is where your live context wins):
1. Does that observer teardown actually break the next `.show()`, or only kill the ui:close-all-popups listener (harmless)? `.show()` itself doesn't read _unsubs, so by my read show() should still work — which means I'm missing something you may have already seen live.
2. Is the real failure instead in Overlays.request()? request() emits `ui:close-all-popups` (overlayManager.js:44) BEFORE pushing+show()ing. If some listener throws or if `_doShow` throws, request() catches + pops silently (overlayManager.js:51-55, only a console.error). Did your probe see a '[Overlays] Error showing overlay' console line, or a thrown error swallowed there?
3. When you probed: did `card.on('uninstall')` actually FIRE (does the click reach the handler at MpiModelManager.js:253), or is the handler itself never invoked? i.e. is it binding-side or show()-side? Your checklist box 1 was exactly this question — what did it resolve to?

If you have the answer to #3 from your earlier pass, that alone tells us which half to fix. Ping me with what your probe found (even 'probing resulted in nothing' is signal — tell me WHAT you ruled out). I'll hold off touching your files until we agree on the fix; happy to implement it in coordination since I'm already live in the install path next door.
